thread.title: Driver stabbed; cab crashes

author: democratandchronicle.com
title: Driver stabbed; cab crashes
text:
A cab driver was stabbed, leading to a car accident, on Ernestine Street in Rochester on Friday afternoon. A 39-year-old Brighton cab driver was stabbed once by a person he was driving, according to Rochester Police Lt. Michael Jones.
Police responded to the area in front of 34 Ernestine St., between Thurston Road and Genesee Park Boulevard, for the report of a crash.
The victim was driving the 41-year-old Rochester resident in an Airway Taxi when the stabbing occurred.
The victim was transported to Strong Memorial Hospital
According to police, charges are forthcoming for the suspect.
WCLEVELAND@Gannett.com
